"n.神权政治 【英】 n.神权政治(governme nt of a state by immediate divine guidance) 【考】 anathema : curse / theocracy : state(anathema是神诅咒/t heocracy是神统治国 家) 【记】 theo(神)+cracy(统治 ); 【同】 参考：autocracy(独 裁统治) n. 神权政治(由宗教权威统治的政府) 【记】theo神, cracy统治: 神权政治. The指独一无二的东西, 原指上帝－神. 【参】theism(n 有神论); atheism(n 无神论); autocracy(n 独裁统治) 【类】anathema: curse = theocracy: stateanathema是神诅咒 = theocracy是神统治国家 【记】theo- the- 神 + cracy统治 【相关】aristocracy 贵族统治，autocracy 专制,democracy 民主, bureaucracy官僚主义,gerontocracy老人统治，gynaecocracy 妇人统治，theocracy 神权政治 theocracy (n.)  1737; earlier as un-Latinized theocraty (1620s), ""form of government in which God is recognized as supreme ruler and his laws form the statute book,"" originally of the sacerdotal government of Israel before the rise of kings, from later Greek theokratia (Josephus), literally  ""the rule of God,"" from theos ""god"" (see theo-) + kratos ""a rule, regime, strength"" (see -cracy). Meaning ""priestly or religious body wielding political and civil power"" is recorded from 1825.  Related: Theocratic (1741)."
